text: Setibhor was an ancient Egyptian queen from the End of the 5th Dynasty. She was most likely the wife of king Djedkare. She had several titles including The one who sees Horus and Seth, the great one of the hetes sceptre, the great of praise and king’s wife, his beloved. Her pyramid was known for a long time and is lying next to that of the king at Saqqara. Her name and titles were found on a column in 2019. == References == Category:25th-century BC women Category:24th-century BC women Category:Queens consort of the Fifth Dynasty of Egypt
title: Setibhor
